cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper proposes a deep learning framework for anatomical segmentation, which involves image processing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a novel approach for label fusion, which involves learning a similarity measure, making it relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses deep neural networks for feature extraction and classification, which is relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on two public datasets, which is relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia).
